    <table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 bgcolor=cfcfbb width=100%><tr><td align=left>
    <font size=3 color="#363636"><b>A use for druids, and a possible game improvement</b></font><br>
    <font size=2>
    Posted on Friday, March 09 @ 22:51:29 EST by <a href="http://www.noows.com">zamtil</a><font size=2>Contributed by: <a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Anonymous">Anonymous</a></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><a href="search.php?query=&topic=30"><img src=images/topics/everquest.gif border=0 Alt="EverQuest" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>Just a suggestion for a possible way druids could be made useful on high level raids, and maybe a fix for a nasty part of the game.
<br><br>
I'm assuming druids are an undesired or useless class on high level raids, just like I've heard from everyone I've asked. Now, this is fairly uncool; druid or not, no class should be in this situation, unwanted on one of the most fun events of EQ. I've also noticed the disturbing tendency of high level mobs who cannot be stunned, mezzed, charmed, or otherwise interrupted to gate away and chain summon an entire raid to their death. This is also not cool; unless there is something I don't know, it seems unfair that a mob could not only get away, but kill an entire raid in an unstoppable and random fashion. (I'm aware of mana drain spells, just not sure that they work to prevent gating.)<br>
<br><br><br><br>You can probably see my idea coming now. I feel Verant should give druids a high casting cost, high recast, quick casting spell that has one function: it interrupts the gate spell, and only the gate spell, regardless of the mobs level. It sure wouldn't unbalance the game, it sure wouldn't overpower druids, and it's effectiveness can be tuned by its level of resistability. It could even be justified RP-wise because druids are masters of gating and banishing summoned, (not that this matters at all.)
<br><br>
Anyhow, I'm sure I'm not the first to think of this. Tell me what's wrong with my idea, and if it actually turns out to be good, spread the word. End Druid uselessness and unstopable mob gating!
<br><br>
I'm not a veteran player, so I'm asking for input, not insults. Be gentle.</td></tr></table><br></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign=top width=200>
